main event: A sighting of an unidentified object with seven powerful white lights observed over Norfolk, Virginia on April 17, 1964.
interesting points: The object was reportedly at high altitude and moved south after the first blast., The sighting was corroborated by other airlines in the area., No missile launch from Cape Kennedy was confirmed during the time of the sighting., Additional information was requested from the report's source but went unanswered., The case is likely attributed to NASA activities, though firm evaluation wasn't possible due to a lack of data.
sighted object: one unidentified object with seven powerful white lights
witness description: crew members of the observing aircraft
